review_text: Underground coffee shops, convenience store. Customers service stand, north and south bus terminals with digital updates of the bus arrivals & departures. Coming soon wheelchair accessible with elevators from street level down to the trains. Best cinnamon buns, made fresh every day. Also many other tasty take away menu items. Agga coffee served here.
Clear map of where to get buses as there are a couple of them

They rejected to allow my bike with flat tires in Sunday afternoon. I had to lock the bike outside and come back to pick it up the next day. They could be a little bit understanding and flexible to encourage using public transport for the citizens.
Still under construction for the past 10 years lol waiting on renovation to see if it gets better. Got pushed by a homeless man. Almost started a random fight
Reaching the 18 bus right as it leaves, at midnight, it's REAL fun to have it completely refuse to wait even one more second.

Standard metro station, dollar store nearby so when you missed your bus in the summer you can go get water and stuff. Construction can be a bit annoying as it changes the layout and bus drop off, 141 is the bus to go to gallery d'Anjou. Shows up most often

As this station serves as the green line's eastern terminus and an important bus depot, it combines elegant modern design with efficiency. A row of entrances along rue Honoré-Beaugrand converge into a large concourse. From there, huge monumental staircases backed with murals by Jean-Paul Mousseau lead to the platforms just beneath the mezzanine level. The platforms themselves expand outwards towards the staircases, as the ceilings rise and fall to break the monotony of the long floors. The platform walls are covered in a frieze of cement, whose slashlike forms express the dynamism of the transit system. Lights hidden behind the nameplates throw dramatic shadows onto the walls.
best metro station in lasalle

(Translated by Google) There was a blond-haired employee from Quebec who was 1.65m tall walking home outside this metro station late at night around 10:30 p.m. on a weekday.
1. Putting his hand in astonishment like I don't know to keep social distancing, it's utterly pitiful.
2. People should be addressed in a more polite manner regarding customer issues. For example, a material loss. Just because you've finished your working day doesn't mean you have to step out of your professional character right away.
Sometimes the 28 bus does not arrive on time. You always have to wait a long time.

(Original)
Il y avait un employé québécois aux cheveux blonds de taille 1.65m qui rentrait chez lui en dehors de cette station de métro tard pendant la nuit vers 22h30 lors d’un jour de semaine.
1. En mettant sa main de façon étonnée comme si je ne savais pas qu’il fallait garder la distanciation sociale, c’est totalement pitoyable.
2. Il faudrait adresser les gens de manière plus polie par rapport aux problèmes des clients. Par exemple, une perte matérielle. Ce n’est pas parce qu’on a fini sa journée de travail qu’on doit tout de suite sortir de son caractère professionnel.
Parfois, le bus 28 n’arrive pas à l’heure. Il faut toujours attendre longtemps.

(Translated by Google) East end of the STM metro network (green line). A large terminus with many exits leading to commercial and residential areas. Large number of trips possible thanks to the STM bus lines and several intermunicipal and regional bus terminals. Several very varied restaurants around.
Located near working-class neighborhoods in the east of the city and giving privileged access to shops and schools (several school boards) ... A little-known place in Montreal that deserves to be explored, you will undoubtedly find great deals and places you'll want to return to.

(Original)
Extrémité Est du réseau métro (ligne verte) de la STM. Un grand terminus avec beaucoup de sorties menant à des aires commerciales et résidentielles. Grand nombre de trajets possibles grâce aux lignes d'autobus de la STM et plusieurs terminus de bus intermunicipaux et régionaux. Plusieurs restaurants très variés aux alentours.
Situé à proximité de quartiers populaires de l'est de la ville et donnant un accès privilégié aux magasins et aux écoles (plusieurs commissions scolaires)... Un endroit méconnu de Montréal qui gagne à être exploré, vous y trouverez sans aucun doute des aubaines et des endroits où vous voudrez retourner.
